00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:58,340
and the lead architect signed the
AIA-G704 Substantial Completion Form.

413
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:02,100
I watched the school district's
moving vans roll onto the campus,

414
00:32:04,740 --> 00:32:05,300
unloading desks and science
equipment into the new wings.

415
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:06,420
My job was done.

416
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:11,440
Ryan and Brad were indicted three months later
on federal mail fraud and state forgery charges.

417
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:16,940
Their trial is still ongoing, but their careers in
corporate finance and contracting are permanently

418
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:22,880
over. As for me, I bought a piece of land in
Montana, overlooking the mountains. I do not

419
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:27,260
wear steel-toe boots anymore, and the only
caliper I use is for woodworking in my shop.

420
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:33,060
Sometimes, when I am drinking my morning coffee,
I think about that rainy afternoon in the trailer

421
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:38,880
when Ryan told me I was barred from the property
and would not get a dime. I smile, take a sip,

423
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:47,980
and look at the mountains, because in the end, if you build a life on a solid foundation
of hard work and honest relationships, no corporate suit can ever tear it down.
